# aka-claude-tools.config — OPT-IN org-specific settings, sourced by aka-claude-tools hooks.
#
# Copy this to the root of your Claude config dir as `aka-claude-tools.config`
# (e.g. ~/.claude-aka/aka-claude-tools.config) and uncomment what you need.
# The installer can place a copy for you. NOTHING here ships by default —
# every value below is empty unless YOU set it.
#
# This is a shell file: `KEY="value"` syntax, sourced by bash. No secrets here —
# these are *patterns to block*, not credentials.

# ── leak-guard.sh (Tier 2) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# A single extended-regex (ERE) of internal identifiers that must never leave in
# a web search/fetch query or an outbound shell command (curl/wget/…): tailnet
# domains, internal IP ranges, VCS usernames, absolute home paths, project
# codenames. Pipe-separate alternatives.
#
# Example:
#   CT_EGRESS_PATTERNS='example-corp\.internal|10\.42\.[0-9]+\.[0-9]+|/Users/jdoe/|acme-vcs-user'
CT_EGRESS_PATTERNS=""

# ── harness-pointer.sh ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Pipe-separated list of command names (matched as the first word) to block,
# plus the hint shown to the agent when one is blocked. Empty = no-op.
#
# Example (team uses a self-hosted VCS, wants to steer away from the GitHub CLI):
#   CT_BLOCKED_CMDS="gh"
#   CT_BLOCKED_HINT="Use plain git — this team's remote is self-hosted, not GitHub."
CT_BLOCKED_CMDS=""
CT_BLOCKED_HINT="This command is blocked by your team's aka-claude-tools harness-pointer."
